brought to room temperature before cooking. For food safety, cook the eggs at least until the whites are cooked through and the yolks have just started to thicken (but they do not need to be hard boiled).","For parents, this dish is lovely on toast, with a little sea salt and pepper to taste. It can also be used as an iron-rich, nutrient-dense butter replacement or dip for any age group."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","30m","1"]}